        <fw type="pageNum">Letter from A. M. Hardin to Mrs. Dismukes; October 7, 1861</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP25139537P0' xml:id='OTP25139537P0'><rs ref='#S51785'>Jackson</rs> Miss Oct. 7. 1861
</p>

<p corresp='TTP25139537P1' xml:id='OTP25139537P1'><rs ref='#S25026765'>Mrs. Dismukes</rs>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP25139537P2' xml:id='OTP25139537P2'>Madam.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP25139537P3' xml:id='OTP25139537P3'>Your husband <rs ref='#S25024608'>Jamison Dismukes</rs> was <rs ref='#S71046'>sentenced</rs> at the <rs ref='#S63231'>Lawrence</rs> <rs ref='#S70054'>Circuit Court</rs> June 6<add place='above'>th</add> 1860 to the <rs ref='#S54861'>Miss Pty</rs>. for 7 years for <rs ref='#S63194'>manslaugter</rs>.
